=== 5.5 The Code: Positional Encoding in Python

The matrix data abstraction from Chapter 2 carries over unchanged.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=matrix]
----

`sinusoidal_position` encodes one position as a vector of alternating sine and cosine values.
Dimension pair stem:[k] oscillates at frequency stem:[\omega_k = 1/10000^{2k/d}], so each position gets a unique fingerprint.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=sinusoidal_position]
----

`sinusoidal_encoding` builds the full stem:[[T \times d\]] matrix by stacking one row per position.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=sinusoidal_encoding]
----

`add_positional_encoding` sums the token embedding matrix stem:[X] with the PE matrix element-wise, giving stem:[\tilde{X} = X + PE].

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=add_positional_encoding]
----

